    narr:narration """This hub answers \"what is the product?\" and its mainline, dated April 28 2026, is positive-identity: the product is [curated expertise installation](narr:Claim_ProductIsCuratedExpertiseInstallation), reaffirming the March 19 Foundation anchor. The session lands as an explicit correction — [the product is NOT a phone number](narr:Claim_ProductIsNotPhoneNumber) — diagnosing the prior tagline as an extraction-pipeline error that confused the text-for-topic experiment channel with product identity. Crucially this does not discard SMS: [the phone number is a distribution channel](narr:Claim_SMSIsDistributionChannel), right in some contexts and wrong in others. Alongside the abstract identity sits a concrete deliverable: [MCP server + 3 interviews at [amount]](narr:Obs_ProductDeliverable), three conversations with CEO, CTO, senior engineer. Two adjacent framings define the system's reach — the [personal/collective-memory graph](narr:Observation_CoreFraming) founding insight and the [lens tool](narr:Observation_ScarletLensDefinition) (competing priorities → different drafts → delta). Style children note code-switching and the 'collective memory' / 'system sketch' metaphors.""" ;
